                  "version": "25.10.4",
                  "date": "2026-06-02T21:27:59.730916",
                  "changelog": "",
                  "checksum": "a89d4c6c8c40e1ba1456e505b5995484e68d6f4b9d82a23252d6e217631a9301",
                  "filesize": 1923203072,
                  "profile": "GENERAL",
                  "train": "TrueNAS-SCALE-Goldeye"
                },
                "release_notes": "## TrueNAS 25.10.4\n\nThis maintenance release updates the Linux kernel and Samba to address multiple security vulnerabilities, and includes ZFS data integrity, NFS, iSCSI, networking, and Active Directory fixes.\n\n- **Security:** Updates the Linux kernel to v6.12.91 and Samba to 4.22.10, mitigating multiple CVEs. Kernel updates include the Dirty-Frag local privilege escalation, a ptrace privilege issue, and the related Fragnesia ESP-in-TCP privilege escalation. Samba updates address a missing access check that let read-only users alter reparse point attributes and a WORM module flaw that allowed protected files to be overwritten through rename.\n- **Critical Bug Fixes:** Fixes a potential ZFS double free when freeing blocks cloned after deduplication table pruning, virtual machines stored on NFSv4.1 datasets failing to power on under VMware ESXi, and a kernel crash in the iSCSI target during SCSI bus or LUN resets on Enterprise High Availability (HA) systems.\n- **HA and Networking Improvements:** Improves iSCSI LUN replacement during HA failover by holding cleanup until cluster coordination completes, and resolves a validation error that incorrectly blocked static network configuration on HA-capable systems when DHCP was not being enabled.\n- **Active Directory Improvements:** Hardens directory rejoin, reset, and recovery handling, improves domain controller selection on systems with multiple controllers, and produces clearer diagnostics when a join or authentication problem occurs.\n- **Additional Fixes:** Resolves ZFS automatic snapshots not being created after a Time Machine backup until the Mac reconnects on macOS Tahoe and later, and reduces excessive winbind log warnings for failed user and group lookups.\n\n**Pre-Update Actions:** null required when updating from 25.10.3.1.\n\n**[Version Recommendations](https://www.truenas.com/software-status/)** | **[Full Release Notes](https://www.truenas.com/docs/scale/25.10/gettingstarted/versionnotes/#25.10.4)** | **[Known Issues](https://www.truenas.com/docs/scale/25.10/gettingstarted/versionnotes/#known-issues)** | **[Enterprise Support](https://support.truenas.com/)** | **[Forums](https://forums.truenas.com/)**\n",
                "release_notes_url": "https://www.truenas.com/docs/scale/25.10/gettingstarted/scalereleasenotes/#25104"
              }
            },
